The paper deals with the topic of distributional semantics, which is a subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of category theory and quantum mechanics in the paper suggests that it may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed methodology for dealing with lexical ambiguity involves algorithms and experimental work, which could fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the use of quantum mechanics in the paper may also make it relevant to systems and control theory (cs.SY).
